  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-c55ec619-7fff-ef73-143b-f503eae24302\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed advertisement, by virtue of its scale, design and positioning, is harmful to visual amenity insofar as it would be harmful to the character and appearance of the locally listed host building; the immediate context; the South Shoreditch Conservation Area; and the wider streetscene more generally, and thus the visual amenity of the area. As such the proposal is contrary policies D4 (Delivering Good Design), (D8 Public Realm) and HC1 (Heritage Conservation and Growth) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP3 (Designated Heritage Assets) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).</span></span><br></p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, design, positioning and method of illumination, would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers by way of light pollution. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering Good Design) and D8 (Public Realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, design, positioning and method of illumination, would result in an unacceptable adverse impact on public safety of highway users by way of driver distraction. As such, the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering Good Design) and D8 (Public Realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP7 (Advertisements) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
